rComments: She's a very good professor,its not her fault that the course requires intense memorization. She makes her tests fair, highlighting the most important points. Need to do all the readings and lectures for an A*.

Lectures are very boring!  Difficult to stay awake.  Extremely unorganized and hardly ever manages to post the lecture notes before lectures.  She is nice but she doesn't make the course interesting and it is very memory intensive. Need to know hundreds of labeling points to get 10 marks on a test. Need to know EVERYTHING (book and lectures)
Wow, somebody actually compared this prof to Professor Rawle...

So-so prof. She has a good clear voice but is somewhat unorganized. Her tests are moderate in difficulty, but she makes you memorize the majority of diagrams in the lectures (there are like 5 per lecture) and then tests you on  2.

Grading criteria is best 3 out of 4 term tests over the full year and an exam. No essays. Exam only cumulative of 2nd semester. SHES a GREAT prof. SHES new so she's enthusiastic. Really VERY easy to talk to and explains things easily. Probabaly one of the best profs after Rawle in terms of wanting everyone to do well and helpfulness. Do Readings!
